Question: Do you think standard tests accurately assess student abilities?
Answer:
i think it really depends on what abilities the tests are trying to measure. logical, technical, and analytical skills can be tested quite easily by math problems and case studies, because they are easy to follow and havehave relatively right or wrongwrong answers. however, skills like writing, music, painting, are hard to be judged good or bad. such creative fields are subjective and depends on inspiration and "feelings".